          "description": "Enjoy an eagle's-eye view by helicopter of high alpine lakes, \"icefalls\" hanging from sheer cliffs, and some of the most remote peaks and glaciers in the Juneau Icefield. Then, your pilot will land in two different locations, where you'll continue your tour on foot to truly appreciate the beauty of this ancient landscape. With your pilot as your guide enjoy 30-minutes of exploration time between these two landings to discover the moraines, crevasses, seracs, and glaciers up close. ",
          "highlights": [
            "Enjoy a 50-minute flight over Juneau Icefield past Wonderland, Glacier King, the Mendenhall Towers, and Devil's Paw.",
            "Trek on foot after landing in two locations and witness firsthand a variety of geological and environmental processes at work."
